The Core Principle: Separation of Concerns
Your project should have at least two distinct parts, living in separate folders:

AI Backend (Your Genkit Flows): This is a dedicated, self-contained service whose only job is to run your AI logic. It receives a request, thinks, and sends back a response.

Frontend/App (Your User Interface): This is what your users interact with. It knows nothing about how the AI works. It only knows how to send a question to the AI backend and display the answer it gets back.

This prevents a bug in your complex AI logic from crashing your entire user application, and vice-versa. Debugging becomes much easier because you know exactly which "zone" the problem is in.

## Recommended Project Structure
The cleanest way to manage this is to have a main project folder that contains sub-folders for your app and your AI functions.

